  • Uses of NetDivinityChoice in it.polimi.ingsw.controller

    Methods in it.polimi.ingsw.controller with parameters of type NetDivinityChoice 
    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void SetupManager.handleGodMessage​(NetDivinityChoice request)
    This method handles the god requests of all players, it sets the game gods when the challenger chooses them (only if all the gods selected are part of the game), it chooses a player's god if it is free (no one has already selected it) and select the starter when the challenger should select it (only if the request's player is the challenger in its active turn during the right game phase).
    void ServerController.updateGods​(ObservableObject observed, NetDivinityChoice playerGods)
    This method receives a request from a client through its RemoteView and analyze if it's the player's turn and if it is the correct phase (the gods phase), if this conditions are all true then the method calls the SetupManager, otherwise it calls the error handling method of the RemoteView.

  • Uses of NetDivinityChoice in it.polimi.ingsw.network

    Methods in it.polimi.ingsw.network with parameters of type NetDivinityChoice 
    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void RemoteView.handleDivinityRequest​(NetDivinityChoice req, boolean error)
    It receives a well formed request of divinity choice, meaning that the divinity exists or all divinity exists and there aren't duplicates if the player is the challenger and is choosing the gods to play with.
    private void ClientMessageListener.parseDivinityInput​(NetDivinityChoice msg)
    This method parses the gods phase messages sending them to the controller and it changes the network phase id a specific message arrives.
    private void ServerClientListenerThread.parseDivinityInput​(NetDivinityChoice divinityMessage)
    This function parses the input that arrives from the client in the gods phase, in this phase the client can choose a god, game gods or the starter (or also disconnect).
